<title>UK: Green Irish pound, Greek drachma to devalue - HGCA.</title>
<headline>Green Irish pound, Greek drachma to devalue - HGCA.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>The green rates of the Irish pound and the Greek drachma will be devalued with effect from Monday, the UK's Home Grown Cereals Authority (HGCA) said on Friday.</p>
<p>The green Irish pound will devalue to 0.759189 per Ecu from the current rate of 0.757666, while the green Greek drachma will devalue to 312.011 per Ecu from 311.858.</p>
<p>Also on Monday, green sterling will enter the fifth and final confirmation period ahead of a possible revaluation on June 5, the HGCA said.</p>
<p>Green rates are used by the European Union to convert Ecus into the currencies of its member states in its Common Agricultural Policy.</p>
<p>--Christopher Lyddon, London newsroom +44 171 542 7928</p>
